-->Welcome to the Quill Guidebook! This book will teach you how to create and format books.
<br/><div styles="h2_purple">Formatting tags:</div>
You can make your text fancier with style tags:
<color><b>bold</b></color><!-- 'b' or 'bold' and 'ub' or 'unbold' -->
<color><i>italic</i></color><!-- 'i' or 'italic' and 'ui' or 'unitalic' -->
<color><u>underline</u></color><!-- 'u' or 'underline' and 'n' or 'derline' -->
<color><s>strikethrough</s></color><!-- 's' or 'strikethrough' and 'us' or 'unstrikethrough' -->
<color><m>magic</m>(magic)</color><!-- 'm' or 'magic' and 'um' or 'unmagic' -->

You can also use whatever <color v="0x32CE5F">color</color> you want with <color>&lt;color&gt;</color> tags. If you really need to, the font can also be changed via a <color>&lt;font&gt;</color> tag.<br/><div styles="h2_purple">Page breaks:</div>
Normally, pages are automatically broken up once the content would overflow into the footer, but you can also manually page break with a <color>&lt;br/&gt;</color> tag.<br/><div styles="h2_purple">Dividers:</div>
<color>&lt;div&gt;</color> tags lets you use styles in addition to the current active style. This is super useful for titles.<br/><div styles="h2_purple">Click Events:</div>
To use a click event, wrap the text you want clickable in a <color>&lt;click&gt;</color> tag. Then, you need to specify the <hover component="hover_clickaction"><click action="OPEN_URL" value="https://javadoc.io/static/net.md-5/bungeecord-chat/1.16-R0.4/net/md_5/bungee/api/chat/ClickEvent.Action.html"><color v="0x3030FF">action</color></click></hover> in an '<color>action</color>' attribute. Some useful actions are <color>OPEN_URL</color> and <color>COPY_TO_CLIPBOARD</color>. Lastly, you need to specify the value, such as a URL, in the '<color>value</color>' attribute.<br/><div styles="h2_purple">Hover Events:</div>
To use a hover event, wrap the text you want hoverable in a <color>&lt;hover&gt;</color> tag. Then, you need to specify the component that gets displayed on hover in the '<color>component</color>' attribute. It is recommended to put this in the book's component cache. You can set the '<color>styles</color>' attribute in a hover tag much like a component tag if you want to set the style of the component that shows up.<br/><div styles="h2_purple">Negative Spaces:</div>
If you're using a resource pack that supports <click action="OPEN_URL" value="https://www.spigotmc.org/threads/440952/">Negative Spaces</click>, then you can make use of it with special tags, such as <color>&lt;_add27&gt;</color> or <color>&lt;_sub11&gt;</color>.
